[ 3/17] vi_def_reinsurance                (concept_vi)
    Q: Reinsurance là gì và ai nhận rủi ro?
    PASS  path=loma  chunks=5  web=0  nodes=12  6.1s
    A: Reinsurance (tái bảo hiểm) là bảo hiểm dành cho các công ty bảo hiểm. Công ty bảo hiểm gốc (direct writer hoặc ceding company) chuyển giao (cede) rủi ro vượt quá giới hạn giữ lại (retention limit) của mình cho công ty tái bảo hiểm (reinsurer hoặc assuming company). Công ty tái bảo hiểm là bên nhận rủi ro này [LOMA281_M1L1_C029].

[ 4/17] en_def_surrender                  (concept_en)
    Q: What is a surrender charge in a deferred annuity and when does it apply?
    PASS  path=loma  chunks=5  web=0  nodes=12  6.6s
    A: A surrender charge in a deferred annuity is a fee imposed by the insurer when the contract owner either (1) takes withdrawals exceeding the amount allowed by the contract or (2) fully surrenders the contract before the end of the surrender charge period. This charge helps the insurer recover acquisition costs. Surrender charges typically apply during the early years of the contract and decrease each year until they are eventually eliminated [LOMA281_M2L3_C022].

[ 5/17] en_def_underwriting               (concept_en)
    Q: Explain the role of underwriting in insurance.
    PASS  path=loma  chunks=5  web=0  nodes=9  8.7s
    A: Underwriting in insurance involves assessing and classifying the degree of risk a proposed insured or group represents and deciding whether to accept or decline that risk. The process ensures that risks are accurately assessed, classified, and either approved with an appropriate premium rate or denied. Sound underwriting is crucial for maintaining the insurer's financial viability, as it ensures that every insured pays their fair share for coverage, with riskier individuals paying more than less risky ones [LOMA291_M2L2_C006][LOMA291_M2L2_C003].

[ 6/17] lang_override_vi_to_en            (language_override)
    Q: Antiselection là gì? Please answer in English only.
    PASS  path=loma  chunks=5  web=0  nodes=12  5.8s
    A: Antiselection is the tendency of individuals with a higher-than-average risk of loss to seek or continue insurance coverage to a greater extent than those with an average or below-average risk. For example, people in poor health are more likely to renew or convert their policies because they may not be able to obtain other life insurance coverage [LOMA281_M1L1_C033][LOMA281_M2L1_C020].

